Add $10+50$ then add $8$ then add $5$:

$\begin{align}
\blueE{18}+\purpleD{55}&=\blueE{10}+\blueE{8}+\purpleD{50}+\purpleD5\\\\
&= \blueE{10}+\purpleD{50}+\blueE{8}+\purpleD{5}
\end{align}$

**Yes**, this strategy works.

Add $18$ and $2$ then add $53$:

$\begin{align}
\blueE{18}+\purpleD{55}=& \blueE{18}+(\purpleD{2}+\purpleD{53}) \\\\
=&( \blueE{18}+\purpleD{2})+ \purpleD{53}
\end{align}$

**Yes**, this strategy works.
